description:
Vermin

The first issue introduces Alina in the role of a monster slayer, tracking the mysterious creature that hunts down peasants around a lake shore. But more than just her sword will be needed - Alina will have to pay a visit to the shadow of her past, that balances between human and foul monstrosity ...
name: Vermin

description: A strange, poetic introduction to the Parallaxium universe. A college student volunteers for a science research project and has an out of body experience that crosses through the Parallaxium into a different universe. The student's visions reveal a medieval world in great peril as the Barrone, a galactic destroyer, approaches devouring all in its path.
Tattooed bookseller-turned-demon hunter Nate Reed endeavors to destroy the supernatural threats that haunt Chicago.
name: Volume One: Lose This Skin

description: Chetek is a quiet town nestled in rural Wisconsin. But when Jonah Schmidt, an Amish carpenter, finds the dismembered bodies of seven teenagers, he uncovers the compromises and consequences of the community that shunned him twenty years ago.

Miguel O'Hara is finally back in his home era, 2099! But there's no time for nostalgia as Spider-Man 2099, Lady Spider and the six-armed Spider-Man are on the run from the ravenous Inheritors! Miguel and Lady Spider bring past and future science to bear, desperate for a clue to help battle Morlun and his family. But can they regroup with the rest of the spiders in time to win the final battle? Then, battered and bloody, Miguel returns to his home dimension to discover that the malicious Maestro has taken charge! Looks like Spidey may have to call in some Strange backup. And Miguel and Peter Parker's worlds collide once again when Alchemax and Parker Industries are caught in a bidding war! Has Miguel's time traveling put his friends in imminent danger?

Collects Spider-Man 2099 (2014) #6-12.
name: Volume 2

description: Teenager Lasha Trinity hates her life. Her best friend is her humanoid dog, Rover. As Lasha tries to deal with her life, an intergalactic war with an alien species looms.

Blood Sisters

Jess and Kelly have nothing in common but good looks and a two-timing, Eastern European boyfriend named Dragos. But when Dragos abruptly leaves town, the two women discover his infidelity is NOT their biggest problem. That's because Dragos is a vampire -- and his parting gift was to turn them both into vampires too! Now these unlikely friends have to work together to deal with blackmailing blood donors, super-cute vampire slayers and the ultimate roommate from hell. Sitcom writer Darin Henry (Seinfeld, Futurama, KC Undercover) and veteran artist Jeff Shultz (Betty and Veronica) have joined forces to bring you a vampire comedy where the vampires are the normal ones! Action! Romance! Sorority Parties! You'll find them all in the hilarious 64 page first issue of Super 'Suckers! Sitcomics -- it's TV you read!
name: Blood Sisters

description:
I took a short (three and a half days!) trip to Iceland in December 2012. This travelogue comic explores my experiences on that trip, and includes art and stories about my second trip to Iceland, in December 2013.

This collection includes all comics and extras from my first three (smaller) books, plus over 30 pages of new watercolors, stories, a glossary, and an Icelandic pronunciation guide.
Vampire Mob continues in comic format!

Vaxdor and The Ikton Conflict

The Evil Iktons are invading the neighboring moon of Locton. A mysterious being know only as Vaxdor, arrives on the planet Ikton. Vaxdor is the most dreaded being in the known universe. He will not stop until the Iktons are defeated.
Vaxdor and the Intruders is a science fiction comic featuring the mysterious alien hero named Vaxdor. Vaxdor and the Intruders was created and written by Troy Vevasis. Art by Lee Milewski.

Dangerous Game of Love

The plan for the night was just like any other for Frank, a three-foot tall, green skinned puppet monster; pull a heist to survive, drowned his regrets in a sleazy speakeasy, and try to find some comfort in the arms of a beautiful woman. But in a place this bad no one manages to stay up for long, and it's Frank's turn to take the fall. One by one the pieces begin to fall into place that will send Frank down a dangerous path that will lead to his doom or deliverance, depending on whether or not he's tough enough to survive what the city has in store for him.

Your Cold Felt Heart is a five issue comic mini-series that blends the moral cynicism and sexual tension of film noir with the extravagant characters and action of vintage pulp hero stories, all told through the silly, playful eyes of puppets.

Your Cold Felt Heart and all its characters were created by Mel Dale, who also writes and draws the comic series, blending his love of crime stories, puppets, and the visual style of the 20s and 30s.
name: Dangerous Game of Love

description:
Judge Dredd // El Maldito (Part: 2)

Mega-City One, 2130 AD. This vast urban nightmare on the east coast of post-apocalyptic North America is home to 400 million citizens, every one a potential criminal. With lawlessness rife, only the Judges can prevent total anarchy. These future lawmen are judge, jury and executioner. Toughest of them all is Judge Dredd - he is the Law!

Demon Nic (Part: 2)

UK, the present day. Demons have walked alongside mankind since the dawn of time, humanity waging war on their species. But now an uneasy peace exists between the two races, and the Church operates as a quasi-military outfit to ensure no demon steps out of line. Cursed with a soul, and an outcast from both sides, Nicodemus just wants a quiet life...

Storm Warning // The Relic (Part: 2)

Brit-Cit, 2137 AD. Much like its Mega-City counterpart, Brit-Cit Justice Department has its various departments, from Tek to plainclothes, Tactical to Psi-Division, and one of its more prickly operatives in the latter is Lillian Storm, a psychically powerful Judge with the ability to talk to the dead. Unfortunately, her abilities are just as much a curse as they are a talent...

Lawless // Between Badrock & A Hard Place (Part: 2)

Colonial Marshal Metta Lawson is appointed to the frontier township of Badrock, and immediately has her work cut out for her bringing order to the colony, where trouble comes in many forms, from droid to mutant to uplift. Will she be able to maintain order where other lawmen have failed?

Cover: Alex Ronald

Action-packed political satire in a post-apocalyptic Western setting, the Jeremiah stories have been worldwide bestsellers since their introduction in the 1980s. Featuring dazzlingly detailed and kinetic artwork from Hermann, a master of European graphics storytelling, the third Jeremiah Omnibus presents tales of blood, vengeance, and the enduring power of friendship.

Jeremiah has sold millions of copies and been translated into 24 languages!

Third omnibus volume from Dark Horse and Strip Arts Features!
